      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/kitab-al-ghayba-numani:2:13:32",
      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/22/2/13/32",
      "text": [
        ": بينا الرجل على رأس القائم يأمر وينهى إذا أمر بضرب عنقه، فلا يبقى بين الخافقين شيء إلاّ خافه."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.abdullah-al-shahin": [
          "(33) Ali bin Ahmad al-Bandaneeji narrated from Obaydillah bin Musa al-Alawi from Ahmad bin Muhammad bin Khalid from his father from Sa’dan bin Muslim from Hisham bin Salim that Abu Abdullah as-Sadiq (as) had said: “As a man is behind al-Qa’im ordering and forbidding, he (al-Qa’im) will order that he is to be killed. Then everything in the world will fear him.”"
        ]
      }
    },
